Release version 1.04
Update documentation about RFC5322

Fix formatting comments which contain nul bytes

According to RFC2822 comment cannot contain unescaped nul byte. So do not
allow to set such comment.

Fix formatting email addresses which contain nul bytes, TAB, LF or CR

According to RFC2822 these characters must be escaped in quoted strings.

When generating address do not escape an apostrophe character

It is not needed according to RFC2822.
Try to parse invalid email addresses and mark them as invalid
Remove duplicate test

Fix generating email address with leading or trailing dot in user part

According to RFC2822, user part in these cases needs to be always quoted.

Fix generating and validating email addresses with empty user part

Such email address is valid according to RFC2822.
Fix docevot parser to disallow leading dot in dot-atom
Replace ',' by '=>' in tests where it makes sense
Replace $undef by undef() in tests where it makes sense
Replace $undef by undef() in POD code examples
Release version 1.03

Do not generate invalid email addresses by format functions

Change format functions to returns empty string when email address is
invalid, e.g. user or host part is missing. Stringified email address
without user or host part is useless and rather disallow generating such
garbage.

Format functions already throw warning when trying to format invalid email
address.

Also change user() and host() methods to validate its input argument,
similarly like address() method does it.
Fix formatting email addresses which user or host part starts with null byte
